      <h3 class="txt-md bold mt-16">1. Vendor Role</h3>
      <p class="txt-xs text-2 mt-4" style="line-height:1.6;">Vendors on PORTDA must be licensed marine service providers. You agree to deliver services as quoted and maintain valid licenses, insurance and statutory approvals.</p>
      <h3 class="txt-md bold mt-12">2. Fees</h3>
      <p class="txt-xs text-2 mt-4" style="line-height:1.6;">PORTDA charges a 5% platform fee on the net order value (excluding GST). Settlement happens within 2 hours of buyer payment via IMPS to your registered bank account.</p>
      <h3 class="txt-md bold mt-12">3. Quality &amp; Disputes</h3>
      <p class="txt-xs text-2 mt-4" style="line-height:1.6;">Cancellation penalty of 5% applies after vendor confirmation. Vendors must respond to buyer reviews within 48 hrs. Repeated complaints may lead to account suspension.</p>
      <h3 class="txt-md bold mt-12">4. Compliance</h3>
      <p class="txt-xs text-2 mt-4" style="line-height:1.6;">Maintain DGS / IRS / IMPA / class certifications as applicable. P&amp;I insurance is mandatory for pilotage and tug operators. Licence expiry warnings are flagged 30 days in advance.</p>
